<item>
            <title>[OAK-1284] Root.commit(String, CommitHook) : CommitHook is not part of oak-api</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1284</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=fmeschbe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;fmeschbe&quot;&gt;fmeschbe&lt;/a&gt; had a look at the oak api and spotted the following problem:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Root#commit(String, CommitHook)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But the CommitHook interface is not part of the OAK API. we quickly searched for usages and found that this is only used for the Item#save case in oak-jcr to assert that the set of modifications is contained with the subtree defined by the specified target item.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IMO we should get rid of the flavour of Root#commit again and solve the Item-save issue differently. For example we could change it to Root#commit(String, String absPath) where the absPath would be the path of the target item...&lt;/p&gt;</description>
